{
  "stem": "21527.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was in the middle of winter, and we heard later that not many of these people survived.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they actually survived most of the war, and were killed just at the end, which was very tragic.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The night of the 15th of January, all of a sudden, there was silence.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The rumbling was stopping and there was silence in the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And everybody was up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Nobody could go to sleep that night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I think there was a feeling that something was about to happen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And my uncle then went to this little guard house where all the guards used to be, guarding the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And he realized that the Germans had gone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And that only a couple of Lithuanian or Ukrainian or something guards were left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He disarmed them, and he actually walked back into the camp with a gun.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we knew we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That was in the early hours of the 16th of January, 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So that for us was the end of the war, but it really wasn't the end of suffering.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "People went crazy.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They started to storm the food stores.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "My uncle tried, sometimes in vain, because he was worried because we had starved for so long, that if people started eating, they would get sick.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And some of them did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Cause we had no-- very little to eat the last few years.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But the Russians had arrived, and we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think they were friendly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were the victors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were the liberating, liberating army.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were pretty wild, some of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They drank a lot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They, they robbed wherever they could.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they were our liberators, so, you know, always have that special feeling for the Red Army, whether you believe in their political leanings or not.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
